💡 Project: Random Quote Generator
🧠 Overview

A Random Quote Generator displays an inspiring, funny, or motivational quote every time a user clicks a button (or refreshes the page).
It’s simple to code, works in any language, and gives contributors lots of room for creativity. 

⚙️ Features

Displays a random quote from a list

Optionally show the author’s name

Allows users to add new quotes via code contributions

Bonus: Add a “New Quote” button or background color changes

🧰 Tech Options

Contributors can pick any language or framework:

HTML/CSS/JavaScript → Simple web version

Python → Console version (prints random quotes)

C++ / Java / Go → CLI version1

React → Web app version with component-based quotes

📁 Folder Example
/projects/random-quote-generator/
 ├── README.md
 ├── quotes.json
 ├── script.py        # or index.html, main.js, etc.
 └── preview.png      # optional screenshot

🧩 Example (Python)
import random

quotes = [
    "The best way to get started is to quit talking and begin doing. - Walt Disney",
    "Dream big and dare to fail. - Norman Vaughan",
    "Code is like humor. When you have to explain it, it’s bad. - Cory House"
]

print(random.choice(quotes))

🪴 Contribution Ideas

Add more quotes to quotes.json

Build the same app in a new language

Style the UI for the web version

Add a button that copies the quote to clipboard
